Telecom Customer Churn and Retention Analysis

Capstone Project – Business Analyst Certification (GCC Employability and Skill Program) – 2025

Project Overview

This project analyzes customer churn behavior for a hypothetical telecom company, JB-Link Telco. The objective was to identify churn drivers, assess revenue impact, and recommend retention strategies using data-driven insights.
The dataset contains 7,044 customer records across 30 variables, including demographic, behavioral, service usage, and billing attributes.

Business Objectives

Identify key factors contributing to customer churn
Measure churn rate and revenue impact
Segment high-risk customer groups
Provide insights to support retention strategies

Dashboard Structure
1. Customer Demographic Overview

Total customers, median age, geographic distribution
Gender distribution and dependent analysis
Referral behavior
Satisfaction rate

2. Usage Trends Analysis

Average monthly charges and tenure
Internet type distribution
Revenue by payment method
Streaming and security service usage

3. Churn Analysis

Overall churn rate (26.54%)
Churn by demographic segments
Churn by risk level
Churn by services and tenure

4. Retention Analysis

Retention rate (67.02%)
Retained customers by value and risk
Retention by internet type and tenure
Customer lifetime value insights

Tools Used

Power BI (Data Modeling, DAX, KPI Development)
Microsoft Excel (Data Preparation)
Data Cleaning and Validation Techniques

Key Insights

High churn observed among senior customers and high-risk segments
Customers using fiber optic services showed higher service engagement
Credit card payment users demonstrated stronger retention patterns
Targeted retention strategies can significantly reduce churn risk

Skills Demonstrated

KPI development and dashboard design
Customer segmentation
Revenue and churn impact analysis
Business insight translation
Structured problem-solving
